# review-panel-discussion drives a discussion-type tool *from inside* an agent
# generation (agent → review-panel tool → nested 3-participant discussion +
# synthesis, all against the CI sandbox's local qwen2.5:0.5b). That nested
# invocation fails in CI with a `fetch failed` at generation time, while the
# standalone discussion run (step 10) succeeds. The tutorial only ever passed
# before because a stale `--discussion` flag silently produced a tool-less
# agent; wiring the tool correctly (discussion_id) exposed the nested-run
# failure. Ignored pending a separate fix to nested discussion-tool execution.
review-panel-discussion
# orchestrate-a-sonnet-with-workflows exercises on_enter agent dispatch, which
